Report on the Special Work of the Local Government Board for the Week ending 20th April, 1917.



1. Among matters which have specially engaged the attention of this Department may be mentioned -

(a) questions in connection with the parliament and Local Elections Bill;

(b) Conferences on the Venereal Disease Bill; 

(c) Electoral Reform and Redistribution of Seats;

(d) Measures to alleviate the financial difficulties of East Coast Towns due to the War.



2. A circular to Local Authorities has been prepared dealing with co-operation of businesses to economise labour, and as to the steps taken with the National Service Department to maintain a sufficient supply of labour for essential sanitary services.



3. The question of the Co-ordination of the Public Health Service has received further consideration.

1 Government Board,

?th April, 1917.
